INSERT INTO `con_about_me` (`id`, `descriptions`) VALUES
(1, '<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Dr. Nizam Uddin Ahmed is a senior public health &amp; management professional with a highly successful background in strategic planning, program design, resource mobilization, partnership &amp; capacity building, research and policy advocacy with Government, NGOs, private sectors through creation and execution of proven strategies. He is working over 30 years in national and international settings with international NGOs, UN Agencies, private sector &amp; INGOs both at Bangladesh and international assignments with varieties of cross-cultural settings in South and Central Asia and provided TA to Asia, USA and Africa region as well.&nbsp; He has solid experiences in health sector including maternal, child health &amp; new-born health, Sexual &amp; Reproductive health, Family Planning, HIV/AIDS, Nutrition program, mHealth/digital health services for management of COVID-19 pandemic He has experiences with donors (USAID, Global Fund, Gates Foundation, CIDA, DFID/UKAID, INGOs and private donors) in large and complex offices and environment for delivering effective outcomes and also experienced in academic researches as well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Dr. Ahmad, himself a dedicated, results-driven health &amp; development professional, has led numerous projects/programs and courses at national and international levels, both in his native Bangladesh and as project leader in other countries in South Asia, Central Asia and Africa. Dr. Ahmad&rsquo;s extensive experiences include the guiding and oversight of various health, emergency &amp; development projects with multi-lateral and bilateral donor organizations. Dr. Ahmad&rsquo;s specific country technical Assistance (TA) include Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan and Uzbekistan, USA and some African nations as well. He has proven ability&nbsp;to navigate large and complex diplomatic challenges&nbsp;to the satisfaction of donors, university, partners &amp; government. He has excellent interpersonal communication and negotiation skills to develop and maintain relationships.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Dr. Ahmed is currently working as CEO in Synesis Health &amp; IT for eHealth and managing largest eHealth National TeleHealth services &ldquo;Shastho Batayon 16263&rdquo; and other eHealth projects with Government and partners and engaged in COVID-19 patients&rsquo; management services, strategic planning and vaccine management resources with government. He utilizes his wealth of knowledge and experiences with advanced ICT for mHealth and eHealth and leading the COVID-19 pandemic responses linking with TeleHealth services and existing health system for its impact on citizen health and achieving Universal Health Coverage towards the SDGs. He is also providing leadership at GAVI CSO SC and Co Founder of &nbsp;Shastho Shurokkha Foundation and associated with other organizations, Universities and professional bodies for making contributions in national goals. He has international higher education, received several trainings &amp; solid professional experiences that has facilitated for transformational education &amp; application of learning in public health, development and creative innovation with team.</span></p>\r\n<h1 class=\"ResumeSectionHeading\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\', sans-serif;\"><strong>Professional Skills:</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Senior level skills and leadership in management of large-scale program with budget of (approx. $7-8 million annually) in Health, Population &amp; Nutrition, HIV/AIDS, and Community Development as Director/CEO and member of Senior Management Team (SMT). </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Strong understanding of Government systems &amp; programs, NGO sector programs and Health sector policies in Bangladesh and South Asia, donors&rsquo; trends and environment, Government 8th Five years plans July 2020- June 2025, collaboration with technical partners/donors in health and other development programs.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Managed large portfolio of eHealth sector in partnership and implementing national TeleHealth services including health, family planning, mental health, ARSH and NCDs with pool of doctors and counsellors in 24/7/365 services </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Leadership in bridging health, development and technology through utilization of IT solutions for greater impact and represented in global forums for Bangladesh </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Planned, designed, and implemented the nation-wide Immunization, Child Survival, Adolescent Reproductive &amp; sexual health, Nutrition and HIV/AIDS prevention and inclusion of HIV/AIDS in national educational curriculum as policy change development partners and Government/MOHFW.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Development project proposal, concept note for mobilizing resources and advocacy strategy for policy change in health sector with partners, Government, donors for results.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Technical knowledge and leadership skills in digital innovation for COVID-19 Pandemic management with partners and implemented National TeleHealth services as Digital Hospital for COVID-19 cases management and vaccination responses. Working as think tank with Government/MOHFW for planning COVID 19 vaccine management and implementation </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Proven ability in representing a senior official for professional discussions and lobby, such as senior Government officials (Minister, Secretary, DGs etc.), donor representatives, Board of Directors of private company, advocacy at national level for results with stakeholders</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Manage large and complex health program including Immunization, MNCH, Family Planning, HIV/AIDS programs at national scale with a budget of approx. 7-8 million annually.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Solid experiences with performance-based funding mechanism, technical assistance and capacity building, grant negotiation, communication to Government and donors and represented at regional, international meetings for supporting country programs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Multi donor coordination with Government, NGOs, civil societies and UN agencies and donors particularly USAID, Global Fund, DFID, Gates Foundation and other bilateral, multilateral and private donors.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Development of partnership in national scale program, strategic planning, resource mobilization, networking with donors for funding, regional collaboration strategies with NGOs, civil societies, private sectors and representation in highest national and international forums. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Prepared work plan, annual and multi-year budgets, monitoring of expenditures &amp; utilization of funds, prepared mission and donor reports. Proven ability&nbsp;to navigate large and complex diplomatic challenges&nbsp;to the satisfaction of donors, implementers, government and organizations.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Manage large project teams with staff supervision and performance evaluations/appraisals.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Training of professional staff and visiting consultants both native &amp; international for high quality results.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Effective proposal development with successful wining of grants through Global Fund, USAID, FCDO (previous DFID), Gates Foundation, EU, INGOs, Government of Bangladesh and other private donors.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Highly effective spokesperson in representing an organization and project to a variety of development audiences that result in successful partnerships for collaborating among various donors and project teams in the health &amp; development aid effort.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Disaster management expertise in health planning, assessment, implementation and management of several national and local disasters in Bangladesh.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Possesses excellent interpersonal communication and negotiation skills and the ability to develop and maintain mutually beneficial internal and external relationships.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Member of several national technical committees, subcommittees and COVID 19 group in health sectors and also engaged in Global Health and social development groups </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Computer skills: MS Ward, MS Power Point, MS Excel, EPI Info, graphics and internet use.</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n