(5, 'Prof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat', '1612183978-9176256.jpg', 'MP, 63 Sirajganj-2', 'chairman', 'https://www.facebook.com/profmhmillat', 'https://twitter.com/profmhmillat', NULL, 'profmhmillat@gmail.com', 'Professor Dr. Md. Habibe Millat is a renowned Cardio-Thoracic surgeon, social worker and prominent political personality in Bangladesh. He is an elected member of Bangladesh Parliament. He represents Sirajganj-2 constituency for the session 2019-2024. He also served as a member of parliament from 2014-2019. Prof. Millat obtained his MBBS from the Mymensingh Medical College, Bangladesh and FRCS from the Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh, UK. He is also trained in Advanced Cardiothoracic Surgery from Europes leading hospitals and in Harvard Medical School, Boston, USA. He has a number of scientific articles published in national and international medical Journals. Prof. Millat is involved in numerous national and international organizations. He is the champion of stopping child marriage and drug abuse, promoting universal health coverage and empowerment of women and youth.\r\n\r\nSome of his positions of responsibilities are mentioned below:\r\n* Former Chairman, Health Advisory Group, Inter-Parliamentary\r\n* Vice Chairman, Bangladesh Red Crescent Society\r\n* Senior Vice Chairman, Bangladesh Medical Research Council\r\n* Member, Standing Committee, Ministry of Foreign Affairs\r\n* Member, Standing Committee, Ministry of Science and Technology\r\n* Former Member, Standing Committee, Ministry of Social Welfare\r\n* Governing Board Member, International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies\r\n* Member, Bangladesh Association of Parliamentarians on Population & Development\r\n* Member, Commonwealth Parliamentary Association, Bangladesh Chapter\r\n* Member, Central Committee, Swadhinata Chikitsak Parishad\r\n* Senate Member, Rabindra University, Bangladesh\r\n* Senate Member, Rajshahi Medical University, Bangladesh\r\n* Professor, Cardiac Surgery, Ibrahim Cardiac Hospital, Dhaka\r\n* Goodwill Ambassador, Bangladesh National Cadet Corps\r\n* Former Chairman, SAARC Medical Research Committee\r\n* Secretary General (Acting), Bangladesh Awami League, Sirajganj District.', NULL, '2021-01-26 08:39:51', 1),
